00:10:22,455 --> 00:10:26,259
He attacked a bar in Ikebukuro
and quit the force.

239
00:10:26,359 --> 00:10:28,428
[ZERO SEVEN]
Do not meddle with this any
further.

240
00:10:28,529 --> 00:10:31,131
[TSUKASA]
I'm in this pretty deep
already...too late.

241
00:10:31,231 --> 00:10:32,799
[ZERO SEVEN]
Well are you sure your boyfriend

242
00:10:32,899 --> 00:10:35,836
would want you getting involved
in all of this mess?

243
00:10:35,936 --> 00:10:38,171
Police officers are all trained
and armed.

244
00:10:38,271 --> 00:10:41,174
I'm armed as well, and I have a
lot of training.

245
00:10:41,274 --> 00:10:43,143
But you do not!

246
00:10:44,144 --> 00:10:45,211
[TSUKASA]

247
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:49,816
[ZERO SEVEN]
Listen...maybe someday...

248
00:10:49,916 --> 00:10:53,153
there will be something safer,
that you can do to help.

249
00:10:55,121 --> 00:10:57,123
[MALE DETECTIVE C]
Kikuhara sir... we've identified
the taxi!

250
00:10:57,223 --> 00:11:00,460
Looks like it was heading
towards uh...

251
00:11:00,561 --> 00:11:02,228
[KIKUHARA]
I found you.

252
00:11:04,698 --> 00:11:05,732
[ZERO NINE]
Are you okay?

253
00:11:05,832 --> 00:11:07,133
[TSUKASA]
I'm always at a loss,

254
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:09,302
wondering if there's anything I
can do to help.

255
00:11:09,402 --> 00:11:12,939
But I was told to just stay
locked up inside.

256
00:11:13,039 --> 00:11:15,709
I hate that, so I went out
anway.

257
00:11:18,879 --> 00:11:20,246
[ZERO NINE]
When you like someone,

258
00:11:20,346 --> 00:11:22,849
it's natural to want to be
useful to them.

259
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:31,191
[ANZAI]
Know myself so I'm not paralyzed
with fear, huh?

260
00:11:31,291 --> 00:11:31,958
And to do that,

261
00:11:32,058 --> 00:11:34,027
I'll need Tsukasa's help.

262
00:11:34,127 --> 00:11:36,863
But I don't want to put
her in any danger.

263
00:11:36,963 --> 00:11:38,231
That's why I've been trying so

264
00:11:38,331 --> 00:11:40,734
hard to put some distance
between the two of us.

265
00:11:41,502 --> 00:11:43,604
That girl. She really isn't the

266
00:11:43,704 --> 00:11:46,072
least bit scared of me, is she?

267
00:11:46,172 --> 00:11:49,710
No...she's never been scared of
me.

268
00:11:49,810 --> 00:11:51,477
She always looks me right in the
eye.

269
00:11:52,345 --> 00:11:53,313
And never hesitates

270
00:11:53,413 --> 00:11:54,881
to do or say anything.

271
00:11:55,816 --> 00:11:56,817
That's what I like about her.

272
00:11:56,917 --> 00:11:58,719
She doesn't fear me.

273
00:11:59,252 --> 00:12:00,220
But that's...

274
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:03,690
exactly why I must never, ever
hurt her.

275
00:12:03,790 --> 00:12:06,426
I have to protect her. And to do
that...

276
00:12:06,527 --> 00:12:09,996
[HANS]
If you're going to rescue her,
I'd like to help.

277
00:12:10,096 --> 00:12:13,767
[ANZAI]
Even though I'm fully aware you
came from ONLO...

278
00:12:13,867 --> 00:12:16,503
In no way does that mean I can
trust you.

279
00:12:16,603 --> 00:12:17,804
[HANS]
Ah well, thanks a lot.

280
00:12:17,904 --> 00:12:21,241
[ANZAI]
But...I can trust you as a
devil.

281
00:12:21,341 --> 00:12:22,308
[HANS]

282
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:23,777
[ANZAI]
The more I want to protect her,

283
00:12:23,877 --> 00:12:26,179
the less I feel like I can get
near her.

284
00:12:27,447 --> 00:12:29,716
If I happen to transform while
in front of her,

285
00:12:29,816 --> 00:12:32,185
can I count on you to keep her
safe from me?

286
00:12:32,853 --> 00:12:34,087
[HANS]

287
00:12:34,187 --> 00:12:35,922
[HANS]
So that whole "I want to protect
her"

288
00:12:36,022 --> 00:12:38,592
thing is your excuse to keep
avoiding her?

289
00:12:38,692 --> 00:12:43,664
I heard you were from ONLO, so I
thought you'd have some kind of
a backbone to work with.

290
00:12:43,764 --> 00:12:46,099
Y'know Tsukasa is never afraid
to confront you.

291
00:12:46,199 --> 00:12:47,500
But you refuse to talk with her

292
00:12:47,601 --> 00:12:50,470
and you do whatever you can to
stay away from her.

293
00:12:50,571 --> 00:12:51,572
Am I right?

294
00:12:51,672 --> 00:12:52,906
I bet you haven't even explained

295
00:12:53,006 --> 00:12:54,040
why you won't get near her.

296
00:12:54,140 --> 00:12:55,976
Talk about immature, leaving out

297
00:12:56,076 --> 00:12:59,145
the important stuff like that.

298
00:12:59,245 --> 00:13:03,183
So if you're gonna keep spouting
that wishy‐washy garbage...

299
00:13:03,283 --> 00:13:06,052
Then maybe I'll just take her
off your hands.

300
00:13:12,325 --> 00:13:15,128
[MAKIMURA]
Zero Five? What are Zero Two's
orders?

301
00:13:16,229 --> 00:13:20,300
Got it. Seven, Nine, and the
hostage.

302
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:22,402
I'll take them out.

303
00:13:22,503 --> 00:13:24,170
[ZERO NINE]
That's not going to be warm
enough.

304
00:13:24,270 --> 00:13:26,873
[ZERO NINE]
Here...Sorry for dragging you
into this.

305
00:13:28,742 --> 00:13:29,910
[ZERO SEVEN]
Something's up.

306
00:13:30,010 --> 00:13:31,612
They found the car a long time
ago,

307
00:13:31,712 --> 00:13:34,014
but I haven't heard any further
orders.

308
00:13:34,114 --> 00:13:37,050
They must be giving out orders
over private channels.

309
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:40,053
We should move. This is where we
need to part ways.

310
00:13:40,153 --> 00:13:43,990
Now, I'm going to call the
police...so you wait here.

311
00:13:44,090 --> 00:13:46,292
There's one thing you need to
know.

312
00:13:46,392 --> 00:13:48,962
Watch for someone named Ushio in
Divison 5.

313
00:13:49,062 --> 00:13:51,532
He has wavy hair and a birthmark
on his face.

314
00:13:51,632 --> 00:13:53,567
He'll be the first one to show.

315
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:55,435
His codename is Zero Five.

316
00:13:55,536 --> 00:13:57,270
[TSUKASA]

317
00:13:57,370 --> 00:13:59,005
[ZERO SEVEN]
I have something in my bag.

318
00:13:59,105 --> 00:14:01,274
We'll let you have it, just in
case.

319
00:14:03,544 --> 00:14:04,477
Please stay safe.

320
00:14:04,578 --> 00:14:05,979
[TSUKASA]

321
00:14:06,079 --> 00:14:08,982
[FEMALERECEPTIONIST]
Yes. I think they're in room
902.

322
00:14:11,985 --> 00:14:16,890
NANNO
Oh my God. Don't
worry, Ma'am, we're the police.

323
00:14:18,625 --> 00:14:19,960
[TSUKASA]

324
00:14:22,896 --> 00:14:25,498
[NANNO]
Tell me. When did the kidnapper
leave?

325
00:14:25,599 --> 00:14:26,967
[TSUKASA]
Just...a while ago.

326
00:14:27,067 --> 00:14:29,603
[ZERO FIVE]
I'll go ahead and carry her out,
Nanno.

327
00:14:29,703 --> 00:14:30,704
She looks pale.

328
00:14:30,804 --> 00:14:32,773
[TSUKASA]
Uh. No, no I'm okay.

329
00:14:32,873 --> 00:14:34,140
I can walk.

330
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:36,977
What do I do? That's Zero Five.

331
00:14:37,077 --> 00:14:38,378
[ZERO FIVE]
Alright.

332
00:14:39,245 --> 00:14:40,346
Then we'll go together,

333
00:14:40,446 --> 00:14:42,148
nice and slow.

334
00:14:42,248 --> 00:14:43,416
[NANNO]
I'll go check on the guys

335
00:14:43,517 --> 00:14:46,787
downstairs. We'll split up, just
in case.

336
00:14:46,887 --> 00:14:48,589
[ZERO NINE]
That was Zero Five.

337
00:14:48,689 --> 00:14:50,156
You uh...think she'll be safe?

338
00:14:50,256 --> 00:14:51,958
[ZERO SEVEN]
I don't think he has any reason

339
00:14:52,058 --> 00:14:53,627
why he'd want to hurt her.

340
00:14:53,727 --> 00:14:54,928
We lost our chance to get out.

341
00:14:55,028 --> 00:14:56,997
And I'm guessing there are cops
downstairs.

342
00:14:57,097 --> 00:14:59,365
[ZERO NINE]
Wh‐what do we do?

343
00:15:05,005 --> 00:15:05,839
[ZERO FIVE]
Look at me.

344
00:15:05,939 --> 00:15:06,973
[TSUKASA]

345
00:15:07,073 --> 00:15:08,509
[ZERO FIVE]
What have you heard?

346
00:15:08,609 --> 00:15:09,943
[TSUKASA]
What do you mean?

347
00:15:10,043 --> 00:15:11,845
[ZERO FIVE]
Did your kidnappers say where

348
00:15:11,945 --> 00:15:14,447
they were going? Or what they're
after?

349
00:15:14,548 --> 00:15:15,448
Or maybe...

350
00:15:15,549 --> 00:15:18,451
That Ushio from Division 5... is
a spy?

351
00:15:18,552 --> 00:15:22,022
<hmph> See there...it's all over
your face.

352
00:15:23,423 --> 00:15:25,125
FEMALE GUEST A
The elevator's here! Hurry up!

353
00:15:25,225 --> 00:15:27,193
BOY GUEST A
Sorry, I'll be right there!

354
00:15:30,564 --> 00:15:31,898
[ELEVATOR VOICE]
The doors are closing.

355
00:15:31,998 --> 00:15:33,667
[TSUKASA]

356
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:35,001
[ZERO FIVE]

357
00:15:35,869 --> 00:15:37,470
[WALLA: HOTEL GUESTS]

358
00:15:39,439 --> 00:15:42,008
[TSUKASA]
Can't believe I did that I
stopped him.

359
00:15:42,108 --> 00:15:43,877
[ZERO SEVEN]
It won't be enough to knock him
out...

360
00:15:43,977 --> 00:15:45,411
[ZERO SEVEN]
So be careful.

361
00:15:45,512 --> 00:15:47,548
[TSUKASA]
I have to get away from this
guy.

362
00:15:47,648 --> 00:15:50,250
But if I go downstairs, I'll run
into him.

363
00:15:52,853 --> 00:15:53,954
[TSUKASA]

364
00:15:54,788 --> 00:15:58,124
[ZERO FIVE]

365
00:16:01,795 --> 00:16:05,732
[TSUKASA]
I can't believe I've
never gotten Anzai's number.

366
00:16:05,832 --> 00:16:08,334
Or Sawazaki's either.

367
00:16:08,434 --> 00:16:11,805
Or Jill's, or Yanagi's, or
Sakaki's...

368
00:16:11,905 --> 00:16:13,073
<realization>

369
00:16:13,173 --> 00:16:14,608
[TSUKASA]
Sakaki...

370
00:16:17,010 --> 00:16:18,545
[ZERO NINE]
Wait, are you serious? You
actually

371
00:16:18,645 --> 00:16:21,047
want to wait on the
roof until the police leave?

372
00:16:21,147 --> 00:16:22,448
[ZERO SEVEN]
Do I look like I'm joking?

373
00:16:22,549 --> 00:16:23,950
[ZERO NINE]
But if we're not careful,

374
00:16:24,050 --> 00:16:25,385
we'll be like rats in a trap.

375
00:16:26,419 --> 00:16:28,689
[ZERO SEVEN]
Nine, get down!

376
00:16:29,923 --> 00:16:31,024
[ZERO NINE]
Zero Seven!

377
00:16:31,124 --> 00:16:32,292
[ZERO SEVEN]
You don't need to worry,

378
00:16:32,392 --> 00:16:33,359
it's just a little scratch.

379
00:16:33,459 --> 00:16:34,761
[ZERO NINE]
But it's... uh...

380
00:16:34,861 --> 00:16:37,030
[ZERO SEVEN]
This is bullshit.

381
00:16:37,130 --> 00:16:38,865
First I'm stabbed in the
stomach,

382
00:16:38,965 --> 00:16:40,066
now I'm getting shot at.

383
00:16:40,166 --> 00:16:42,402
And by humans once on my side.

384
00:16:42,503 --> 00:16:46,239
And here I thought the devils
were my only real enemy to
avoid.

385
00:16:46,339 --> 00:16:48,408
[ZERO NINE]
Don't forget I'm human.

386
00:16:48,509 --> 00:16:50,243
And I'll be with you till I die!

387
00:16:50,343 --> 00:16:52,245
[ZERO SEVEN/NANAKO]

388
00:16:52,345 --> 00:16:55,315
[HANS]
If you're gonna keep spouting
that wishy‐washy garbage...

389
00:16:55,415 --> 00:16:57,618
Then maybe I'll just take her
off your hands.

390
00:16:57,718 --> 00:17:00,554
[ANZAI]
You better watch your mouth. I
mean it.

391
00:17:00,654 --> 00:17:02,088
[HANS]
I'm just sayin'.

392
00:17:02,856 --> 00:17:03,957
[ANZAI]
Lay a hand on her,

393
00:17:04,057 --> 00:17:04,891
and I will kill you.

394
00:17:04,991 --> 00:17:05,959
[HANS]
Oh yeah?

395
00:17:06,059 --> 00:17:08,428
I'd like to see you try.

396
00:17:08,529 --> 00:17:09,395
[ANZAI]

397
00:17:09,495 --> 00:17:10,130
[JILL]
Anzai!

398
00:17:10,230 --> 00:17:11,164
You have a call! It's

399
00:17:11,264 --> 00:17:12,833
Tsukasa‐she's looking for you.

400
00:17:12,933 --> 00:17:13,767
She called the bar!

401
00:17:13,867 --> 00:17:15,101
[ANZAI]

402
00:17:15,201 --> 00:17:17,671
[TSUKASA]
Anzai? I'm so glad I got you!

403
00:17:17,771 --> 00:17:19,806
[ANZAI]
Tsukasa! Are you okay? Where are
you?

404
00:17:19,906 --> 00:17:22,543
[TSUKASA]
At a place called the Mino Hotel
in Tsukiji.

405
00:17:22,643 --> 00:17:25,211
[ANZAI]
Ok. What about the sniper? I
thought you were her hostage.

406
00:17:25,311 --> 00:17:29,850
[TSUKASA]
She just let me go free. But now
there's some other person after
me instead.

407
00:17:29,950 --> 00:17:31,317
[ANZAI]
Somebody else?

408
00:17:31,417 --> 00:17:33,153
[TSUKASA]
The sniper warned me about him.

409
00:17:33,253 --> 00:17:36,056
[TSUKASA]
She said Ushio in Division 5 was
a spy.

410
00:17:36,156 --> 00:17:37,691
[ANZAI]

411
00:17:37,791 --> 00:17:39,860
[TSUKASA]
I thought that he'd see me if I
went downstairs...

412
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:41,528
so I came up to the higher
floors...

413
00:17:41,628 --> 00:17:44,698
[ANZAI]
Do you see anywhere you can
hide?

414
00:17:44,798 --> 00:17:47,701
[TSUKASA]
I think I can get into room
1424.

415
00:17:47,801 --> 00:17:51,437
[ANZAI]
Okay. I'll be right there. You
stay in that room.

416
00:17:51,538 --> 00:17:54,040
[TSUKASA]
Um...I'm sorry, Anzai...

417
00:17:54,140 --> 00:17:56,743
I said a lot of things I
shouldn't have.

418
00:17:56,843 --> 00:17:58,211
I'm sorry.

419
00:17:58,311 --> 00:18:00,647
[ANZAI]
There is nothing to
be sorry about!

420
00:18:00,747 --> 00:18:02,215
You wait for me right there!

421
00:18:05,118 --> 00:18:07,120
ELEVATOR VOICE
Fourteenth floor.

422
00:18:09,455 --> 00:18:11,592
[ELEVATOR VOICE]
The doors are closing.

423
00:18:12,559 --> 00:18:14,160
[ZERO FIVE]
Excuse me, sir.

424
00:18:15,061 --> 00:18:17,197
[TSUKASA]

425
00:18:20,033 --> 00:18:21,401
[TSUKASA]

426
00:18:23,103 --> 00:18:24,404
[ZERO FIVE]

427
00:18:26,540 --> 00:18:28,509
[ZERO FIVE]
There you are.

428
00:18:28,609 --> 00:18:31,177
Why don't we just end this now?

429
00:18:32,613 --> 00:18:36,349
[ANZAI]
The first time I saw her...I
thought... she was cute.

430
00:18:37,684 --> 00:18:40,020
Just an innocent girl who'd
never have anything

431
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:42,322
to do with the underbelly of
society.

432
00:18:44,090 --> 00:18:48,061
That's why I was so glad I found
her before she became his next
victim.

433
00:18:48,161 --> 00:18:53,099
<scoff> Listen to me?! Why am I
even thinking about this right
now?

434
00:18:53,199 --> 00:18:54,735
[ZERO FIVE]
Come over here.

435
00:18:56,036 --> 00:18:57,237
You don't need to worry.

436
00:18:57,337 --> 00:18:59,940
I'll kill you as painlessly as
possible.

437
00:19:00,040 --> 00:19:03,276
[TSUKASA]
But why? Why do you have to kill
me in the first place?

438
00:19:03,376 --> 00:19:05,612
[ZERO FIVE
Cause I'm not ready to leave
Division 5.

439
00:19:05,712 --> 00:19:10,551
I can't have you going around
telling people I'm a spy for the
CCC, can I?

440
00:19:10,651 --> 00:19:12,452
[TSUKASA]
CCC?

441
00:19:12,553 --> 00:19:15,155
[ZERO FIVE]
The Chosen Civil Community.

442
00:19:15,255 --> 00:19:17,791
A fellowship of elect citizens.

443
00:19:17,891 --> 00:19:19,059
[TSUKASA]

444
00:19:19,159 --> 00:19:20,827
[TSUKASA]
You call a group of murderers

445
00:19:20,927 --> 00:19:22,629
"chosen"? Are you insane?

446
00:19:22,729 --> 00:19:25,431
[ZERO FIVE/USHIO
Is that a problem?

447
00:19:25,532 --> 00:19:26,833
[TSUKASA]
It makes no sense!

448
00:19:26,933 --> 00:19:28,268
You're killing people, but the

449
00:19:28,368 --> 00:19:30,470
name makes it sound like it's
the right thing to do!

450
00:19:30,571 --> 00:19:31,838
[ZERO FIVE]
That's your opinion.

451
00:19:31,938 --> 00:19:34,207
Whether it's right or not is a
separate issue.

452
00:19:34,307 --> 00:19:37,578
[TSUKASA]
Then tell me. Why is it you hold
a grudge against devils?

453
00:19:37,678 --> 00:19:39,780
[ZERO FIVE]
I don't. I actually like them.

454
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:41,181
[TSUKASA]
What?

455
00:19:41,281 --> 00:19:44,084
[ZERO FIVE]
I feel so sorry for them
sometimes.

456
00:19:44,184 --> 00:19:45,786
I work with devils on the
force...

457
00:19:45,886 --> 00:19:48,488
And when there's an injured
human on the scene...

458
00:19:48,589 --> 00:19:51,558
They always look like they're in
so much pain.

459
00:19:51,658 --> 00:19:54,127
They clench their fangs,
fighting their bloodlust...

460
00:19:54,227 --> 00:19:56,096
Begging for sedatives.

461
00:19:56,196 --> 00:19:57,664
[ZERO FIVE/USHIO
All the while, being treated

462
00:19:57,764 --> 00:20:00,834
like monsters by the very people
they saved.

463
00:20:00,934 --> 00:20:03,103
I can't help but pity them.

464
00:20:03,203 --> 00:20:05,171
When I see a devil in pain like
that...

465
00:20:05,271 --> 00:20:08,341
I want to free them from
all their suffering.

466
00:20:08,441 --> 00:20:11,311
Free them from their cursed
fate.

467
00:20:11,411 --> 00:20:12,879
[HANS][ANZAI]

468
00:20:12,979 --> 00:20:15,081
[HANS]
So this Ushio guy... Know what
he looks like?

469
00:20:15,181 --> 00:20:16,216
[ANZAI]
How should I?

470
00:20:16,316 --> 00:20:18,985
I can't trust Division 5
anymore.

471
00:20:19,085 --> 00:20:20,787
I'll have to rescue her myself.

472
00:20:21,788 --> 00:20:22,789
Tsukasa!

473
00:20:22,889 --> 00:20:25,926
Why do I always end up putting
you in danger?

474
00:20:27,093 --> 00:20:28,529
[TSUKASA]
Then why?

475
00:20:28,629 --> 00:20:29,763
If you care so much about them,

476
00:20:29,863 --> 00:20:31,998
why are you out here trying to
kill them?

477
00:20:32,098 --> 00:20:33,499
If you care for them, shouldn't

478
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:35,569
you try to come up with a way to
coexist?

479
00:20:35,669 --> 00:20:37,871
[ZERO FIVE]
That's just your ego talking
now.

480
00:20:37,971 --> 00:20:41,207
It's not like you ever had to
try and live their sad life.

481
00:20:41,307 --> 00:20:43,610
You don't know what they have to
suffer through.

482
00:20:43,710 --> 00:20:45,779
[TSUKASA]
Isn't that true for you, too?

483
00:20:45,879 --> 00:20:48,815
You've never had to live a
devil's life, either!

484
00:20:48,915 --> 00:20:52,485
But you talk about freeing them,
like you know what they want.

485
00:20:52,586 --> 00:20:54,621
You just take their lives from
them.

486
00:20:54,721 --> 00:20:58,959
Don't act self righteous! You
are judging them!

487
00:20:59,059 --> 00:21:00,193
[ZERO FIVE]

488
00:21:00,293 --> 00:21:02,262
[ZERO FIVE/USHIO
I was wrong about you.

489
00:21:03,964 --> 00:21:06,099
[ZERO FIVE]
I thought you'd be begging for
your life,

490
00:21:06,199 --> 00:21:08,001
but you're lecturing
me instead.

491
00:21:08,101 --> 00:21:12,205
That tends to make people angry,
if you haven't noticed.

492
00:21:12,305 --> 00:21:14,374
Either you have nerves of
steel...

493
00:21:14,474 --> 00:21:16,476
Or you're just plain stupid.

494
00:21:19,445 --> 00:21:20,847
[TSUKASA]

495
00:21:20,947 --> 00:21:23,750
[ZERO FIVE]
But I don't really care which
one it is.

496
00:21:25,151 --> 00:21:26,687
[ANZAI]

497
00:21:38,464 --> 00:21:40,166
[YOUNG ANZAI]

498
00:21:40,266 --> 00:21:41,434
[KIKUHARA]
Are you scared?

499
00:21:41,535 --> 00:21:44,404
Everyone here surrounding us is
a devil.

500
00:21:44,505 --> 00:21:46,640
Just like you are.

501
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:48,575
[ZERO FIVE]

502
00:21:49,543 --> 00:21:50,911
[HANS]

503
00:21:59,319 --> 00:22:04,858
[ANZAI]

504
00:23:42,656 --> 00:23:43,924
[ANZAI][TSUKASA]
Devil's Line.

505
00:23:44,725 --> 00:23:46,426
[ANZAI][TSUKASA]
Line Eight.

506
00:23:46,527 --> 00:23:47,894
[ANZAI][TSUKASA]
Offline.

